Given a (uniform) hypergraph H and a vertex u. An absorber for u is a subgraph A of H which consists of the following edges specified in the properties below:


  * A contains a Berge cycle C with u∈ V^*(C) of length 2t+1 for some t∈ and with vertex sequence
(u,v_1,…,v_t+1,…, v_2t);

  * there are t-1  Berge paths P_1, …, P_t-1 so that each path P_i has endpoints v_i+1 and v_2t+1-i and the inner vertex sets are pairwise disjoint; 


  * the edge-sets E(C), E(P_1),…, E(P_t-1) are pairwise disjoint;

  * E(A)=E(C)∪⋃_i∈ [t-1]E(P_i).

We call the vertex u a reservoir vertex and the absorber A a u-absorber . The inner vertices of A are the vertices from V^*(C)∪⋃_i V^*(P_i). The vertices v_1 and v_t+1 are referred to as the main endpoints of A.

